  "text": "• monophyly. Phylogenetic analyses clearly separate EAV, LDV, PSSRV, and SHFV into four clades. These analyses are based on the similarity of the ORF1b nucleotide sequences or the encoded pp1b amino acid sequences and/or on homologous and alignable portions of coding-complete viral genomes (thus excluding the additional 4 SHFV ORFs) [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] ; and • host range. EAV, LDV, PRRSV, and SHFV are known to infect equids, rodents, suids, and nonhuman primates, respectively.",
